alert.note: Alert for Lewis; Pierce (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued December 06 at 9:44AM PST until December 06 at 4:35PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Washington... South Prairie Creek at South Prairie affecting Pierce County. Cowlitz River At Randle affecting Lewis County. Nisqually River Near National affecting Lewis and Pierce Counties. Newaukum River Near Chehalis affecting Lewis County. Chehalis River At Porter affecting Grays Harbor County. ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Washington... Chehalis River Above Grand Mound affecting Thurston and Grays Harbor Counties. ...The Flood Warning is cancelled for the following rivers in Washington... Puyallup River Near Orting affecting Pierce County. .Heavy rain is over but flood waters continue to make their way down rivers and streams. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL LATE THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...No flooding is currently forecast. * WHERE...Nisqually River near National. * WHEN...Until late this afternoon. * IMPACTS...At 6,000.0 cfs, the Nisqually River will locally spill over its banks along the upper reaches of the river downstream to Alder Lake. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 9:00 AM PST Wednesday the flow was 7,540.0 cfs. - Flood flow is 8,000.0 cfs. - Forecast...The river fell below flood flow this morning and to continue to fall. Flooding will continue as the flood wave makes its way down the river. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by this morning at 1045 AM PST.
